# PR Management Instructions

When asked to manage a PR or prepare PR content, provide the following:

## 1. Changelog Message (PAST tense)
Short message describing what was fixed/added/changed. Use past tense.

**Example:** `Fixed MySQL migration compatibility with sql_require_primary_key`

## 2. Commit Message (PRESENT tense, conventional commit format)
Use conventional commit format: `type: description`

Types: `fix`, `feat`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`

**Example:** `fix: MySQL migration with sql_require_primary_key enabled`

## 3. PR Content (use this template)

```markdown
## Scope

What's changed:
- [Main change 1]
- [Main change 2]
- [Technical detail if relevant]

## Potential Risks / Drawbacks

- [Risk 1 or "None" with explanation]
- [Risk 2]

## Tested Scenarios

- [Test scenario 1]
- [Test scenario 2]

## Review Notes / Questions

- [Important note for reviewers]
- [Any pattern references or special attention areas]

## Checklist

- [ ] Added or updated tests
- [ ] Documentation PR created [here](https://github.com/directus/docs) or not required
- [ ] OpenAPI package PR created [here](https://github.com/directus/openapi) or not required

---

Fixes #<issue_number>
```

## Style Guidelines

- Be concise and direct
- No fluff or marketing language
- Technical but readable
- Reference existing patterns when applicable
- Mention what's NOT affected to reassure reviewers
